verbose_text: In the presence of 2 mM guanosine triphosphate (GTP) serving as a nucleophile in the cleavage reaction (XREF_FIG) and 50 mM Mg 2+ ions contributing to RNA folding and catalysis, a catalytic amount (0.1 muM) of Syn Rz and Azo Rz showed multiple cleavage of the substrate RNA (1.0 muM) (XREF_FIG).
